iResiliency conjures up this idea that our writing is somehow		gopher.black	70
ieither indelible or written in disappearing ink. Some people will		gopher.black	70
iassuredly make the choice to nuke their archives and skip out on		gopher.black	70
igopher or the web or whatever. Some will have hardware failures or		gopher.black	70
iplatforms will go away. Others will surely continue to archive.		gopher.black	70
iCameron Kaiser will continue his efforts, or others will rise up		gopher.black	70
iand do the same, and much of this will survive in someone's text		gopher.black	70
iarchives. Others will come and go from places like SDF, leaving		gopher.black	70
ibehind a few postings and files before forgetting their account		gopher.black	70
iexists. tfurrows has four cosmic posts [2] and five more secret		gopher.black	70
igopher postings [3] that link up a really cool and interesting		gopher.black	70
iscience fiction story. If that story doesn't continue then it		gopher.black	70
istill exists as part of the shared universe. It adds to the vibe		gopher.black	70
iand contributes in itself.		gopher.black	70
